The paper discusses a model for reforming publishing in physics, which involves preprints and journal review articles. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on scholarly communication and publishing, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
